  interesting, and convenient place to stay. It's great for families with kids, 
  and easy to find a big space to split between a group. 
  
  Here are a few hotels in the Berkeley/Oakland area:
  
  - [Doubletree Hilton Berkeley Marina](http://doubletree3.hilton.com/en/hotels/california/doubletree-by-hilton-hotel-berkeley-marina-JBKCADT/index.html)
  
  - [Courtyard Marriot Emeryville](http://www.marriott.com/hotels/travel/oakmv-courtyard-oakland-emeryville/)
  
  - [Claremont Hotel Club & Spa](www.claremontresort.com/)
  
  - [Hotel Shattuck Plaza](http://www.hotelshattuckplaza.com/)
  
  And a few in San Francisco:
  
  - [Marriot Union Square](http://www.marriott.com/hotels/travel/sfous-san-francisco-marriott-union-square/)
  
  - [Hyatt Regency](http://sanfranciscoregency.hyatt.com/en/hotel/home.html)
  
  - [Argonaut Hotel](http://www.argonauthotel.com/)
  

  
  If you're planning to camp, there are a handful of beautiful 
  campsites within minutes of Oakland and Berkeley, namely the [Chabot 
  Regional Park](http://www.ebparks.org/parks/anthony_chabot). More info at 
  [ebparks.org](http://www.ebparks.org/activities/camping)  
    
